doc.after: Kenyans generally have three meals in a day breakfast in the morning kiamsha kinywa lunch in the after noon chakula cha mchana and supper in the evening chakula cha jioni or known simply as chajio In between they have the 10 o clock tea chai ya saa nne and 4 pm tea chai ya saa kumi Breakfast is usually tea or porridge with bread chapati mahamri boiled sweet potatoes or yams Ugali with vegetables sour milk meat fish or any other stew is generally eaten by much of the population for lunch or supper Regional variations and dishes also exist
